@DanielHaywood bro i have a ps5 pro , xbox X, and a 4080 super pc with a 9900x amd cpu liquid cooled that cost me almost $3k.
Let me tell you that if you only want to game then ps5 pro is the best deal in the world!!  
Yeah my pc gives me higher FPS but after 120 fps you cant really tell the difference, and the graphics are exactly the same on ultra settings as the ps5 pro! Only difference is better ray tracing. Only good thing is that you can use a high end pc for other things besides gaming. But if you only want to game then a PC is such a waste of money ! Get PS5 pro better!

@TheGameBench on TSMCs own website:

The 4nm (N4) process technology is an enhanced version of 5nm (N5) technology

In other words, its 5nm+ not a new process

@Kevinwoolford123 The 4090 was a big jump in performance compared to the 5090.
I'm using a 4070 TI came from my old and trusty 1080 TI strix, so the performance gain  which was over twice as much, was worth it for the 800 dollars at release.
I'm aiming at the 70 series next so they have time to fix the problems that will occur with these generation of cards.

@JustVC Price of a PS5 Pro is completely fine dude. Stop letting the opinions of others influence that of your own.

If I'm wrong, build a PS5 Pro equivalent PC without using second hand parts for LESS than 700 USD, since that the price of the PS5 Pro is already considered ''horrible''.

Good luck.
